"From the beginning, I tried to keep a clear dictation with both and then with the choir, so that you can understand the text well, so that a harmony can be established," said the conductor.
The Czech national anthem will celebrate its 175th anniversary next year.
The song Kde domov můj was first performed in 1834 on the stage of the Standetheater in the original Czech piece Fidlovačka by Josef Kajetán Tyl, the music of František Škroup.
It became popular, and people spontaneously accepted it.
The first verse of the song then became an organic part of the national anthem after the emergence of Czechoslovakia in 1918.
