The drivers who can fall back because of the alcohol level will have to install the 'Alcolock'.
The authority orders that the driver, who had three official penalties for the alcohol level, install this system in his car, which forbids him to start the car in a drunken state. If he is alcoholized, then the car does not start.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the General Public Prosecutor's Report. It is a pilot project, which will last for a year.
The purpose is to re-socialise the driver, which is why he receives a course for the re-education of traffic behaviour.
The Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for the Safety of Automobiles will also participate in this, except for the Public Prosecutor General's Office, as experience shows.
According to statistics, between 30-75% of drivers who were shown more than once because of driving under the influence of alcohol were taxed.
The `alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the exhaled air and prevents auto start when the driver has done the alcohol test; or if an alcohol concentration is detected which is higher than permitted.
It costs more than 1 000 euros, the costs are borne by the person who imposes the penalty.
In this context, a study conducted in the United States in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with these devices prevented up to 65% of the regulatory violations in the first year after its introduction.
In Spain it is estimated that 115 lives could be saved every year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to tackle this behaviour before it becomes a criminal offence.
And in order to facilitate their implementation, a legal reform can be implemented in the ordinary way, yet a reform of the basic law is required which is necessary for the law enforcement process.
The device is still available on the Spanish markets, in no business, although it has already been installed in some commercial vehicles and public transport vehicles.
