"An additional effort is necessary - he adds - in terms of communication and awareness-raising of public opinion.
But above all, a greater sense of responsibility on the part of employers is in need of a phenomenon which is a social emergency."
Mercandelli also pointed out "the progressive deterioration in the protection of victims of accidents at work" and urged "the abolition of the social system against which we have been fighting in recent years".
"The aim is therefore to return to the worker a guarantee of insurance so that the fate of the victim of an accident at work does not depend on voluntary or accidental donations that are decided upon by a legislator from time to time".
Mp3 Player under Charge: Hazard of Hearing Damage
Sound music over a longer period of time with portable music devices, such as Mp3 players, can lead to permanent hearing damage.
